    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "That seems like a strange design to me - if the rules are a class level attribute then there is no instance   level data stored on the class and all the methods could be classmethods and the user would never have to actually instantiate the subclass to use it.\n\nIt also seems contrary to [`AbstractHolidayCalendar.__init__`](https://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/a72d95163b4d268012709255d7a52bbe5c1a7eb6/pandas/tseries/holiday.py#L281) which specifically allows overriding the rules at an instance-level.\n"
